args: All right! There's just one fiend\nleft in the village!
I don't see it. Where could it be?
Whiskers just ran outside!\nCome back, Whiskers!
The distance is too great to cover on foot.\nThis is a gamble, but... Haaah!
If one can control the flow of air itself,\nany foe is but a rock. Now fall! Haaah!
Nicely done, Ku Hai! Was that chi kung?
Indeed. It is a binding technique\nin which one releases their chi\nto immobilize a distant opponent.
My command of it is somewhat shaky,\nso I usually refrain from using it.\nI am pleased it turned out well.
I am relieved to hear that.
You're like that traveling man we met!
You met someone else who can\nwield that technique?!
Yeah. Whiskers runs away a lot, see?
And one time, this man said ＂HAH!＂ like\nyou just did, and she froze in place so\nI could run over and pick her up.
Tell me more about him! TELL ME!
...My apologies. I should not have\nlost my composure in such a manner.
A while back, a traveling swordsman\ncame to stay with us.
In return for room and board, he worked\nthe fields and looked after my daughter.
What was his name? And do you know\nwhere he was headed next?
Oh dear. It was three years ago,\nso I'm not sure if... Oh!
Your sword! He had one just like it!
By the heavens... That was Haoran!
Someone you know, I take it?
He was super nice to us, just like you!\n...Well, except when you get all yell-y.
Thank you for telling me this.
Can I ask you something, Ku Hai?
Yes. I've never seen you lose composure\nlike that, and it got me wondering about\nthat Haoran fellow you mentioned.
He was a student at the dojo in Peng Lai,\nand a fellow disciple of Master Xuan.

He was more skilled at releasing his chi,
while I excelled at using it to strengthen
my body. Our skills became a natural
complement to each other.
Releasing chi was what you did earlier,\nright? Is that how you knew the girl\nwas referring to him?
That, plus the fact he had a sword the\nsame as mine. Such weaponry is given\nonly to those who attended my dojo.
So why are you searching for this man?
Judging by your reaction when you heard\nabout him, I'm guessing it's nothing good.
Do you remember when I told you\nthat my master had passed away?
He did not suffer a natural death.\nHe was murdered...by Haoran.
One day, several years ago, I left the dojo\nto attend to some other business.
The next day, I returned to find my\nmaster's lifeless body.
His wounds were clearly the work\nof Haoran's skilled swordsmanship,\nbut I have not seen him since.
After that, I turned my back on my\nhomeland and struck out on a journey.
This was partially to inherit my deceased\nmaster's will, but in truth, I also wanted\nto track down Haoran.
And what will you do when you find him?\nDo you plan to avenge your master?
Haoran respected our master\nmore than anyone else.
I do not understand why he would kill him,\nso I plan to ask and find out.
Then let me help you find him.
No. This is my own matter, and I will\nnot trouble you with it.
But the more people searching,\nthe better the chance of finding him.
Besides, the problems of my friends are\nmy problems too. I can't just ignore them.
I cannot believe you would go so far\nto aid a simple wanderer such as me.
But as you seem bent upon it,\nI will accept your kind offer.
